<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO INDUSTRY NOTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 John A. Doede has increased his stake in San Diego-based Crown Bancorp from 
10.48% to 12.24%, or 79,727 common shares. Doede, who was given approval by the 
Federal Reserve Bank of San Francisco to acquire control of Crown, purchased 
24,500 shares between May 16 and May 23 for from $4 to $4.75 each, or a total 
of $116,000, according to a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission. 
</P>
</TEXT>
