<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY EARNINGS: COM SYSTEMS REPORTS $801,000 GAIN IN QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Com Systems, a long-distance telephone company serving Western states, said its 
earnings in the first quarter that ended March 31 rose 55% to $801,000. Sales 
increased 56% to $19.6 million. 
</P>
<P>
The Van Nuys company said its results are improving in part because of 
acceptance of its 800 number, international calling, calling card and voice 
messaging services. 
</P>
