<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY ROUNDUP: NU-MED COMPLETES SALE OF 3 SERVICE SUBSIDIARIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nu-Med said it finished selling three of its health care service subsidiaries 
to a new company formed by Kidd Kamm &amp; Co., a Beverly Hills investment 
group. According to an earlier filing with the U.S. Securities and Exchange 
Commission, Nu-Med was to receive $45 million in cash. 
</P>
<P>
The sale includes NSI Services, which provides skilled nursing services to 
hospitals; Home X-Ray Services of America, a mobile X-ray service, and National 
Healthcare Review, a consulting service. The annual revenue of the three units 
is about $74 million. 
</P>
