MORNING REPORT: STAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Claudia Puig, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Controversial director and writer Charles Marowitz is expected to replace the 
recently resigned Richard Stayton as theater critic at the Los Angeles 
Herald-Examiner, beginning next week. Except for two previously contracted 
directing jobs, Marowitz will suspend his work in the theater while serving as 
the newspaper's critic, he said. A resident of Los Angeles since 1981, he is 
best known locally for his work at Los Angeles Theatre Center and its 
predecessor, Los Angeles Actors' Theatre; he resigned in March as the theater's 
associate director in charge of dramaturgy and editor of its magazine Alarums 
&amp; Excursions. Claudia Puig 
