<P>
A medical report on the Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini said Iran's 89-year-old 
leader is recovering well from surgery to stop internal bleeding, and he was 
shown on Iranian television sitting in his hospital bed, being fed soup and 
playing with a grandson. Iranian opposition sources said, however, that 
Khomeini's condition may be much worse than officially reported. A statement 
from the Baghdad-based Moujahedeen organization, released in Bahrain, said 
Khomeini had suffered a heart attack since the operation last week and that he 
previously had required prostate surgery. Iranian television mentioned a slight 
heart complication on Saturday but gave no details. 
