<HEADLINE>
<P>
3 DEAD, 1 MISSING AS BOATS CRASH IN FLORIDA WATERWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
INDIAN ROCKS BEACH, Fla. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A search was resumed Monday for a teen-ager missing after a 35-foot-long 
high-powered boat collided with a 17-foot pleasure boat on the Intracoastal 
Waterway, killing at least three people on the smaller boat. None of those 
aboard the larger boat were seriously injured in the collision Saturday. The 
crash was under investigation. 
</P>
