TODAY'S QUOTE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"I could see this was the answer from the beginning. . . . I thought it would 
be mandated in every school district in the country by now." 
</P>
<P>
 -- Los Angeles Deputy Police Chief Glenn Levant, who oversees the department's 
anti-drug DARE program, which began in 1983 as a pilot project in 50 Los 
Angeles grade schools. 
</P>
