<HEADLINE>
<P>
JULIAN GUNFIGHT LEAVES TWO DEAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two people were shot and killed Monday night in a gunfight that sent sheriff's 
homicide detectives to the east side of Julian. An unknown number of suspects 
were still at large, and the motive for the shooting was unknown. 
</P>
<P>
Sheriff's dispatcher Leslie Roeder said one of the victims was dead before 
authorities reached the scene about 7 p.m., and the other was pronounced dead 
by the Life Flight medical crew after it arrived. 
</P>
<P>
Roeder said the shooting occurred along the highway about a quarter of a mile 
west of the Banner Store in the 36300 block of Banner Grade Road, near the 
bottom of the grade as California 78 winds eastward from Julian. 
</P>
<P>
Roeder said further details were unknown because of poor radio communications 
between detectives at the scene and sheriff's dispatchers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
