<HEADLINE>
<P>
TARZANA MAN'S DEATH RULED STRANGULATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An autopsy has determined that a 74-year-old Tarzana man, whose body was found 
in his apartment on Friday evening, died of strangulation, the coroner's office 
reported Monday. 
</P>
<P>
The body of Harry Simon of 18375 Collins St. was already decomposing when it 
was found, said Michael Riddle, an investigator with the Los Angeles County 
coroner's office. This made it difficult to determine the cause of death 
without an autopsy. 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles Police Department homicide detectives were investigating. 
</P>
</TEXT>
