<TEXT>
<P>
Peter Longbottom, 30, of Britain, the oldest rider in the Milk Race, won the 
first stage of the 13-day bicycle race around England and Wales by edging 
Czeslaw Rajch of Poland in a final sprint. 
</P>
<P>
Longbottom, Rajch and a large pack of other racers all finished the 121.5-mile 
stage from London to Bournemouth, England, in 4 hours 41 minutes 22 seconds. 
</P>
