ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: FOUNTAIN VALLEY; 
</P>
<P>
MINIATURE GOLF COURSE HOLDUP NETS $11,000 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two armed men in ski masks forced their way into the office at a miniature golf 
course Monday morning, tied up the assistant manager and made off with $11,000 
in cash and the assistant manager's pickup truck, police reported. 
</P>
<P>
The assistant manager, Steve D. White of Fountain Valley, was released by other 
employees, who found White bound to a post in the video arcade at the Family 
Fun Center on Magnolia Street at the San Diego Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
The holdup occurred shortly after 7 a.m., when White arrived at work, police 
said. They quoted White as saying he heard knocks at the door, thought they 
came from employees appearing for work and opened the door. 
</P>
<P>
Instead, there were two disguised men armed with handguns who forced White to 
open the office safe. 
</P>
