<P>
IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
S. AFRICAN STOPS AMERICAN IN 6TH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, South Africa 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
South African heavyweight champion Pierre Coetzer knocked American 
cruiserweight Mike Greer down twice, then stopped him in the sixth round of a 
scheduled 10-round bout Monday night. 
</P>
<P>
Greer, of Memphis, Tenn., was booed by the crowd from the outset as he went 
straight into clinches and held on, hardly throwing a punch. Greer, ranked 
fourth by the International Boxing Federation, fifth by the World Boxing 
Council and sixth by the World Boxing Assn., was the highest-rated opponent 
Coetzer has faced in his bid for a chance at the world heavyweight title. 
Coetzer improved his record to 26-2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
